AGI - Macabre discovered by the workers working at the excavation of Piazza Pia, the work symbol of the Jubilee a few meters from St. Peter: a human skeleton was found a few meters under the road. It should be treated, explaining by the State Archaeological Superintendency that intervened on the spot, of a skeleton dating back to the 17th-XVIII century of a person probably of the people.
&nbsp;
Even in the past there was a chapel in that area, it seems unlikely that it was a skeleton buried there as found devoid of any fungi. More information on the skeleton, dating of death and sex, will be provided by autopsy and instrumental examinations. Despite the finding, the work continued without interruption. &nbsp;

