AGI - The rector of the Catholic University Franco Anelli was found dead > Thursday evening 23 May in the inner courtyard of the palace in which he lived in the center of Milan. The 60-year-old lawyer and jurist committed suicide > launching from the sixth floor of the palace in which he lived. The alarm was taken around 22.30 and rescuers from 118 arrived on the spot who could only declare the death. Anelli was in charge of the athenaeus with offices in Milan, Rome, Brescia, Cremona and Piacenza since 2013 and would expire at the end of October.
&nbsp;
The prosecutor of Milan will open a file on his death, a technical passage to carry out all the investigations of the case, including autopsy. The gesture of Rings, however, is considered a suicide, without the involvement of other people. From the first coat of arms of the carabinieri in the double apartment in which the rector lived with the long-time companion there would be no farewell messages.> According to what was reconstructed, around 22:30 the professor would go out of the house and reach the sixth and last floor of the building of Via Luigi Illica from which he would have thrown himself in the inner courtyard.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> Bipartisan policy framework
"With sadness we learned the news of the disappearance of prof. Franco Anelli,&nbsp;Rettore&nbsp; of the Catholic University of Milan," says M5s exponents in cultural commission to the Chamber and the Senate. "At this time of great pain, we join in the mourning of the family, friends and all the academic community," a note continues. "Profondo cordoglio" is also manifested by the president of the Constitutional Affairs Committee of the House, Nazario Pagano, along with the "vicination with the academic community of the Catholic University and the Political Foundation Universitario Gemelli". "His dedication to education, training and academic progress has left an indelible mark in the history of the Catholic University and in the Italian university landscape. Professor Anelli was an example of integrity, commitment and passion for knowledge, values he has transmitted to generations of students and colleagues." "His loss leaves a deep void not only in the academic community, but throughout the country. At this time of great pain - concludes the exponent FI - I wish to express my sincere condolences to the family of Professor Anelli and to all those who have had the honour to know and work with him". "My deepest sympathy and closeness to the family of prof. Franco Anelli and to all the academic community of the Catholic University and the University Polyclinic Foundation Agostino Gemelli IRCCS, who lost a man of extraordinary culture and educational vision," says also the vice president of Action, Elena Bonetti.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2>The note of the Catholic University and Gemelli&nbsp;></h2>
"In the late evening of yesterday, in his Milanese home, the Magnificent Rector of the Catholic University Professor Franco Anelli has tragically disappeared under investigation circumstances," we read in the note issued by the University. "With deep consternation the Community of the Catholic University > and of the University Polyclinic Foundation Agostino Gemelli IRCCS>, to which he devoted his work and his entire life - he adds - he gathers in regret and prayer, expressing the most felt condolence to his mother and loved ones". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> The condolence of the EC and the Crui></h2>
"I participate in the pain of the Catholic University and the Fondazione Policlinico Agostino Gemelli Irccs for the tragic disappearance of the Magnificent Rector, Professor Franco Anelli". It is the condolence message of the president of the Cei, Cardinal Matteo Zuppi>. "At this moment of dismay, on behalf of the Italian Episcopate, I express my condolence to his mother, to his loved ones and to the whole community of the University and the Polyclinic, which he dedicated his existence. I assure the prayer of our Church, entrusting dear Professor Anelli to the mercy of the Father."
&nbsp;
"Profondo turbamento" has also been expressed by the Conference of Rectors and the entire university system that "closed today around the academic community of the Catholic University and the Anelli family in expressing the deep condolence for the sudden disappearance of the &nbsp;rettore&nbsp;Franco Anelli". "Franco was above all a friend - commented commossa Giovanna Iannantuoni, President of CRUI> -. A deeply ironic man with a rare coherence to meet. We'll miss him very much."

